WHO   — The 10NES Lockout — the gatekeeper · ethereal
WHAT  — the gatekeeper · ethereal
WHERE — NES · THE NES (exereunesis · the teardown)  Framework inputs: chip; bus; spec  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — The CIC lockout chip: a console-and-cartridge handshake meant to block unlicensed games. When it failed to sync — often from a dirty connector — the console reset in a loop. The famous blinking power light, in part, was this chip saying no.
HOW   — Rendered from the public technical record.

